<body>
Reports unreachable statements inside SQL routines.
<p>Example (Microsoft SQL Server):</p>
<pre><code>CREATE FUNCTION foo() RETURNS INT AS
BEGIN
    THROW;
    RETURN 1;
END;</code></pre>
<p>In Microsoft SQL Server, the <code>THROW</code> statement raises an exception and transfers execution to the CATCH block of the TRY...CATCH
  construct. Therefore, the <code>RETURN 1;</code> part will never be executed.</p>
</body>
